{"id": "duc04-testb-24:14#43", "contents": "Saramago, a known atheist, dismissed the Vatican's disapproval of his achievement, saying that the Vatican should focus on its prayers and leave people alone. He quipped that if the Pope had been among the jury, he wouldn't have won the prize. The writer's comments were made during a packed press conference in Madrid, where he also spoke about his upcoming book, \"The Cavern,\" which deals with a modern version of Plato's myth of the cave. Saramago's win was widely celebrated in Portugal, with daily papers dedicating ample space to the event, and Lisbon City Hall hanging up posters congratulating the author."}
